Conf . on Database and Expert System Applications ( DEXA 2000 ) - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - The importance of information systems that are able to deal with spatial data is ever growing . A particular challenge is the capability to meet advanced requirements for spatial data , such as temporally changing spatial data , uncertainty in spatial information , or relationships and constraints between collections of spatial objects . We solicit papers that present new ideas with regard to : - data models - query languages - query processing and optimization - index structures - spatial reasoning - user interfaces - specification methods - prototyping - system architecture - interoperability that help to promote advanced spatial data management in the following areas ( and possibly others ) : - spatio-temporal data - complex spatial data ( maps , networks , . . . ) - constraint spatial data - spatial uncertainty - spatial data and the WWW - robust geometric computation - advanced applications PROGRAM CHAIRS : Martin Erwig FernUniversitaet Hagen , Germany Markus Schneider FernUniversitaet Hagen , Germany Timos Sellis National Technical University of Athens , Greece PROGRAM COMMITTEE ( to be expanded ) : Dave Abel CSIRO , Australia Eliseo Clementini University of L'Aquila , Italy Max Egenhofer University of Maine , USA Andrew Frank Technical University Vienna , Austria Stephane Grumbach INRIA , France John Herring Oracle , USA Klaus Hinrichs University of Muenster , Germany Manolis Koubarakis Technical University of Crete , Greece Yannis Manolopoulos Aristotle University Thessaloniki , Greece Beng Chin Ooi National University , Singapore Dimitris Papadias Hongkong University of Science and Technology , China Jan Paredaens University of Antwerp , Belgium Philippe Rigaux CNAM Paris , France Yannis Theodoridis Computer Technology Institute , Greece Agnes Voisard Freie Universitaet Berlin , Germany Ouri Wolfson University of Illinois , USA Michael Worboys Keele University , United Kingdom PAPER SUBMISSION : We invite submissions of papers describing original , previously unpublished research . Please send a full paper in postscript ( A 4 or letter format , readable by ghostview ) or PDF to asdm 2000 @ stc . hac . sw Papers should not exceed 8 pages and must not be submitted simultaneously elsewhere . Accepted papers will be published by IEEE Computer Society Press .
